Mox pro εἷς τὰ τρία eidem Ficinus legisse videtur εἰς τὰ τελευταῖα. Fortasse εἰς τᾶ τρίτα scripsit Ploti- nuS, si cogites, Marsilium non usquequaque ver- bum verbo reddere solere, ut proinde τᾶ τρίτα ex rationis Plotinianae indole accipere potuerit pro postremis.—Taylor in Epistola ad me data haec de hoc loco: “ In this place for αὐτὴν it is requi- site to read αὗτόν. For Plotinus is here speak- ing of the soul when in the intelligible world, and says that through intellect it perceives and proceeds to the good. And in line 4 of the same page for εἷς τὰ τρία it is necessary to read, con- formably ‘to the version of Ficinus, εἰς τὰ τελευ- ταῖα. For frequently in bodies the medium ad- mits of a progression from things that are first to such as are last.”
